{"article_id":"6Sl8KBFu6KIcVARh","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Trump Signs New Order","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"Blocking Arrivals From 6 Majority-Muslim Countries","depth":2},{"id":2,"text":"President Trump has signed a new executive order","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"that temporarily blocks visas from being issued to citizens of six majority-Muslim countries ,","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"revoking and replacing a controversial , now-suspended executive order","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"known as the travel ban .","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"Like the initial order","depth":10},{"id":7,"text":"signed Jan. 27 ,","depth":10},{"id":8,"text":"the new executive order bars arrivals from specific majority-Muslim countries for 90 days","depth":10},{"id":9,"text":"and suspends the entire U.S. refugee program for 120 days .","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"It also caps the total number of refugees","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"admitted this fiscal year","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"at 50,000 , instead of 110,000 .","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"But there are a series of differences .","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"The ban","depth":13},{"id":15,"text":"announced Monday","depth":13},{"id":16,"text":"no longer includes Iraq .","depth":12},{"id":17,"text":"It explicitly does n't apply to lawful permanent residents","depth":14},{"id":18,"text":"( green card holders )","depth":14},{"id":19,"text":"or existing visa holders .","depth":13},{"id":20,"text":"Syrian refugees are not banned indefinitely .","depth":13},{"id":21,"text":"Refugees","depth":15},{"id":22,"text":"already formally scheduled for travel to the U.S.","depth":15},{"id":23,"text":"will be permitted to enter the country .","depth":14},{"id":24,"text":"The new order also omits a section","depth":12},{"id":25,"text":"about prioritizing refugees from minority religions in their home countries .","depth":12},{"id":26,"text":"That 's the part of the initial order","depth":13},{"id":27,"text":"that ,","depth":14},{"id":28,"text":"as NPR 's Domenico Montanaro has reported ,","depth":15},{"id":29,"text":"`` indicates prioritizing Christians , ''","depth":15},{"id":30,"text":"and was one reason","depth":13},{"id":31,"text":"the order was challenged as a form of `` Muslim ban . ''","depth":13},{"id":32,"text":"The order","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"signed Monday","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"will have a delayed implementation","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"- going into effect at 12:01 a.m . ET on March 16 -","depth":11},{"id":36,"text":"to avoid the chaotic situation","depth":11},{"id":37,"text":"created by the initial order ,","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"with people in transit","depth":11},{"id":39,"text":"when their visas were nullified .","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"The new order blocks people traveling from Sudan , Syria , Iran , Libya , Somalia and Yemen .","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"Iraq is no longer included","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"because ,","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"the administration says ,","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"it has pledged to `` increase cooperation with the U.S. '' and share more information about its citizens .","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"A senior administration official told reporters about another reason :","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"Iraq has agreed to the `` timely repatriation '' of Iraqi citizens in the U.S.","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"who are slated for deportation ,","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"the official said .","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"As of last summer , Iraq was one of 23 countries","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"considered `` recalcitrant ''","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"for refusing to cooperate with the U.S.","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"in deporting their citizens .","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"`` Recalcitrant countries '' were raised as an issue in a separate executive order ,","depth":6},{"id":54,"text":"but were n't mentioned in either of the orders on visas and travel .","depth":6},{"id":55,"text":"Some `` recalcitrant '' countries ,","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"including Iran and Libya ,","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"are affected by the visa ban ;","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"most are not .","depth":7},{"id":59,"text":"Administration officials left open the possibility","depth":7},{"id":60,"text":"that other countries could be added to future visa-issuance bans ,","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"or that countries currently on the list could be removed .","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"The White House has consistently said","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"that the travel ban was not and is not a `` Muslim ban , ''","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"but a policy","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"designed to reduce the threat of a terrorist attack .","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"Critics of the travel ban have challenged the selection of the seven","depth":12},{"id":67,"text":"( now six )","depth":12},{"id":68,"text":"countries ,","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"questioning","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"whether it can be justified on any fact-based national security grounds .","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"The seven countries were on an Obama administration list of `` countries of concern '' for the Visa Waiver Program ,","depth":11},{"id":72,"text":"which had nothing","depth":12},{"id":73,"text":"to do","depth":13},{"id":74,"text":"with blocking travel entirely .","depth":13},{"id":75,"text":"As NPR 's Greg Myre has reported ,","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"the list `` does n't include any countries","depth":13},{"id":77,"text":"from which radicalized Muslims have actually killed Americans in the U.S. since Sept. 11 , 2001 ''","depth":13},{"id":78,"text":"- like Saudi Arabia , Egypt , Pakistan or Russia .","depth":12},{"id":79,"text":"The latest executive order apparently attempts to address this with a paragraph about `` conditions '' in each targeted country , and the terrorist groups with a presence or connection there .","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"`` Each of these countries is a state sponsor of terrorism ,","depth":13},{"id":81,"text":"has been significantly compromised by terrorist organizations ,","depth":14},{"id":82,"text":"or contains active conflict zones , ''","depth":14},{"id":83,"text":"the new order states ,","depth":12},{"id":84,"text":"alleging","depth":12},{"id":85,"text":"that the countries pose `` heightened risks '' to U.S. security .","depth":12},{"id":86,"text":"The suspension of the U.S. refugee program has been similarly criticized .","depth":9},{"id":87,"text":"Since the Refugee Act of 1980 , there have been no deadly terror attacks by refugees .","depth":7},{"id":88,"text":"Nine people were injured in an attack by a Somali refugee last year ,","depth":8},{"id":89,"text":"which is still under investigation .","depth":8},{"id":90,"text":"In Monday 's executive order , the administration offered three examples of people","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"who entered the U.S. as refugees","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"and were convicted of terrorism-related offenses .","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"Two came from Iraq ;","depth":9},{"id":94,"text":"they are the men","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"who lived in Bowling Green , Ky. ,","depth":11},{"id":96,"text":"and were charged with supporting a terrorist group .","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"Another came from Somalia as a child refugee","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"and was arrested","depth":11},{"id":99,"text":"for plotting an attack on a holiday event in Portland , Ore .","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"He was a naturalized U.S. citizen by the time of his arrest .","depth":9},{"id":101,"text":"Speaking on Monday ,","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"Attorney General Jeff Sessions also said","depth":9},{"id":103,"text":"that `` people","depth":10},{"id":104,"text":"seeking to support or commit terrorist attacks here","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"will try to enter through our refugee program . ''","depth":9},{"id":106,"text":"He said","depth":8},{"id":107,"text":"hundreds of people","depth":11},{"id":108,"text":"who arrived as refugees","depth":11},{"id":109,"text":"are under FBI investigation for possible terrorism-related crimes ,","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"although the Department of Justice has refused to provide any details about these reported investigations .","depth":9},{"id":111,"text":"The White House insists","depth":8},{"id":112,"text":"the first order was legal and appropriate ,","depth":8},{"id":113,"text":"even though it 's being replaced by the new order .","depth":7},{"id":114,"text":"That original order prompted chaos at airports","depth":9},{"id":115,"text":"and inspired protests","depth":9},{"id":116,"text":"- and dozens of lawsuits .","depth":8},{"id":117,"text":"The suits were filed by `` doctors , professors , students , people","depth":12},{"id":118,"text":"fleeing violence","depth":12},{"id":119,"text":"and Iraqis","depth":12},{"id":120,"text":"who have worked for the U.S. military , ''","depth":12},{"id":121,"text":"as NPR 's Joel Rose and journalist Parker Yesko reported last month .","depth":10},{"id":122,"text":"They continued :","depth":10},{"id":123,"text":"`` Some","depth":13},{"id":124,"text":"[ of the plaintiffs ]","depth":14},{"id":125,"text":"were detained in American airports for hours over the weekend ;","depth":14},{"id":126,"text":"others were barred overseas from boarding planes","depth":13},{"id":127,"text":"bound for the U.S.","depth":13},{"id":128,"text":"Two Syrian brothers with visas","depth":14},{"id":129,"text":"to enter the country","depth":14},{"id":130,"text":"say","depth":13},{"id":131,"text":"they were turned around at Philadelphia International Airport","depth":13},{"id":132,"text":"and sent back to Damascus . ``","depth":13},{"id":133,"text":"Human rights organizations and attorneys general in five states jumped aboard some of the suits ,","depth":11},{"id":134,"text":"and their lists of legal grievances were long .","depth":11},{"id":135,"text":"They alleged violations of the First , Fifth and 14th Amendments ,","depth":12},{"id":136,"text":"which guarantee religious equality , due process and equal protection under the law ,","depth":12},{"id":137,"text":"as well as denials of asylum and discriminatory visa processing . ''","depth":11},{"id":138,"text":"One of the suits ,","depth":13},{"id":139,"text":"brought by the state of Washington","depth":14},{"id":140,"text":"and joined by the state of Minnesota ,","depth":14},{"id":141,"text":"prompted a federal judge to issue a nationwide temporary stay of Trump 's executive order on Feb. 3 .","depth":12},{"id":142,"text":"The Department of Justice challenged the stay in a U.S. appeals court ,","depth":12},{"id":143,"text":"but a panel of three judges upheld the suspension .","depth":12},{"id":144,"text":"As a result , the initial executive order has not been in effect for more than a month .","depth":10},{"id":145,"text":"The new order ,","depth":9},{"id":146,"text":"which is twice as long as the original ,","depth":9},{"id":147,"text":"is meant to `` address previous concerns '' from the courts ,","depth":8},{"id":148,"text":"according to Homeland Security Secretary John Kelly .","depth":7},{"id":149,"text":"But it 's not likely to be the end of legal challenges .","depth":8},{"id":150,"text":"`` I think everyone","depth":12},{"id":151,"text":"- and","depth":13},{"id":152,"text":"I assume","depth":14},{"id":153,"text":"the government as well -","depth":14},{"id":154,"text":"expects","depth":11},{"id":155,"text":"that there will be a new round of litigation , ''","depth":10},{"id":156,"text":"Omar Jadwat , director of the Immigrants ' Rights Project at the ACLU , told NPR","depth":10},{"id":157,"text":"before the new order was released .","depth":10},{"id":158,"text":"In a statement Monday , he said","depth":8},{"id":159,"text":"the new order is `` a scaled-back version","depth":9},{"id":160,"text":"that shares the same fatal flaws . ''","depth":9},{"id":161,"text":"Meanwhile , the signing of a new executive order does n't necessarily spell the end of lawsuits against the old order .","depth":4},{"id":162,"text":"White House press secretary Sean Spicer has repeatedly said","depth":6},{"id":163,"text":"the administration plans follow a `` dual track '' strategy","depth":8},{"id":164,"text":"of continuing to defend the old order from legal challenges","depth":8},{"id":165,"text":"even as a new order replaces it .","depth":7},{"id":166,"text":"However , the executive order","depth":11},{"id":167,"text":"signed Monday","depth":11},{"id":168,"text":"formally revokes the Jan. 27 order as of March 16 ,","depth":10},{"id":169,"text":"and a senior official at the Department of Justice told reporters on Monday","depth":10},{"id":170,"text":"that the DOJ believes","depth":11},{"id":171,"text":"a majority of the pending cases are now moot .","depth":11},{"id":172,"text":"That may well spell the end for many of those suits , especially those","depth":9},{"id":173,"text":"brought on more narrow grounds .","depth":9},{"id":174,"text":"But whether or not a lawsuit is still valid will be decided case by case .","depth":7},{"id":175,"text":"Judges might not necessarily be persuaded by the Justice Department 's arguments","depth":10},{"id":176,"text":"that a case is no longer relevant ,","depth":10},{"id":177,"text":"says Catherine Kim , a law professor at the University of North Carolina Law School .","depth":9},{"id":178,"text":"She joined other law professors","depth":10},{"id":179,"text":"in signing an amicus brief against Trump 's initial order ,","depth":10},{"id":180,"text":"and spoke to NPR","depth":10},{"id":181,"text":"before the new order was announced .","depth":10},{"id":182,"text":"Even for cases","depth":12},{"id":183,"text":"where the original complaint is no longer an issue under the new order","depth":13},{"id":184,"text":"- like , for instance , a case","depth":14},{"id":185,"text":"involving a lawful permanent resident -","depth":14},{"id":186,"text":"`` the courts may be worried","depth":11},{"id":187,"text":"that","depth":11},{"id":188,"text":"as soon as the case is dismissed","depth":12},{"id":189,"text":"the administration would just go back","depth":13},{"id":190,"text":"and reissue the [ original ] executive order , ''","depth":13},{"id":191,"text":"Kim says .","depth":9},{"id":192,"text":"Other , broader challenges to the original order could apply equally to the new order ,","depth":11},{"id":193,"text":"she says","depth":11},{"id":194,"text":"- such as the allegation","depth":12},{"id":195,"text":"that the order was `` done in bad faith , ''","depth":12},{"id":196,"text":"she says .","depth":11},{"id":197,"text":"`` I do n't think","depth":11},{"id":198,"text":"that there is anything","depth":13},{"id":199,"text":"that the new executive order could do","depth":13},{"id":200,"text":"to address concerns","depth":14},{"id":201,"text":"raised by the courts","depth":14},{"id":202,"text":"[ that ] this was really motivated by animus , not by national security concerns , ''","depth":13},{"id":203,"text":"she says .","depth":10},{"id":204,"text":"The Trump administration maintains","depth":5},{"id":205,"text":"that it will eventually triumph in the legal battle over the original executive action ,","depth":6},{"id":206,"text":"based on the president 's broad authority on immigration issues .","depth":6},{"id":207,"text":"Some legal scholars ,","depth":8},{"id":208,"text":"including Alan Dershowitz ,","depth":8},{"id":209,"text":"believe","depth":7},{"id":210,"text":"the administration could win at least a partial victory on those grounds .","depth":6},{"id":211,"text":"`` I do n't think","depth":9},{"id":212,"text":"the ban is unconstitutional","depth":9},{"id":213,"text":"as it affects a family in Yemen","depth":9},{"id":214,"text":"who has had no contact with the United States","depth":10},{"id":215,"text":"and simply applies for a tourist visa","depth":11},{"id":216,"text":"to come see the Statue of Liberty , ''","depth":11},{"id":217,"text":"he told NPR in early February .","depth":7},{"id":218,"text":"But ,","depth":9},{"id":219,"text":"Dershowitz said ,","depth":9},{"id":220,"text":"other elements of the ban","depth":10},{"id":221,"text":"- especially the initial interpretation","depth":11},{"id":222,"text":"that it applied to green card holders -","depth":11},{"id":223,"text":"are harder to defend .","depth":9},{"id":224,"text":"The issue could eventually end up before the U.S. Supreme Court .","depth":7}],"relations":[{"parent":449,"left":226,"right":448,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":226,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":448,"left":384,"right":447,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":384,"left":285,"right":383,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":285,"left":276,"right":284,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":276,"left":229,"right":275,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":229,"left":227,"right":228,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":227,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":228,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":275,"left":262,"right":274,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":262,"left":235,"right":261,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":235,"left":232,"right":234,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":232,"left":230,"right":231,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":230,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":231,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":234,"left":233,"right":12,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":233,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":261,"left":253,"right":260,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":253,"left":13,"right":252,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":252,"left":244,"right":251,"relation"